<div class="header1">
Get tourfilter on your desktop
</div>
<div id="main-full-width">
<p>With a single click, you can subscribe to tourfilter show calendars in OS X's iCal (pictured) and many other calendaring applications. Try it!</p>
<ul>
<%
	host_and_port=request.host
	host_and_port+=":#{request.port}" if request.port!="80"
%>
<li>
	<% if @youser_known%>
	<span style="vertical-align:-30%">
		<a border=0 href="webcal://<%=host_and_port%>/<%=@metro_code%>/ical/<%=@youser.name%>"><img border=0 src="/images/ical.gif"></a>
				or
	<span style="vertical-align:-30%">
		<a href="http://www.google.com/calendar/render?cid=http://www.tourfilter.com/<%=@metro_code%>/ical/<%=@youser.name%>"><img src="http://www.google.com/calendar/images/ext/gc_button1.gif" border=0></a>
	</span>
		<a href="webcal://<%=host_and_port%>/<%=@metro_code%>/ical/<%=@youser.name%>">Subscribe to just my tourfilter shows.</a>
	</span>
	<% else %>
	<span style="vertical-align:-10%">
		<a border=0 href="#" onclick="alert('You must be logged in to do that!');"><img border=0 src="/images/ical.gif"></a>
	</span>
	<a href="#" onclick="alert('You must be logged in to do that!');">Subscribe to just my tourfilter shows.</a>
	<%end%>
	</li>
	<li>
		<span style="vertical-align:-10%">
				<a border=0 href="webcal://<%=host_and_port%>/<%=@metro_code%>/ical"><img border=0 src="/images/ical.gif"></a>
				or
		<span style="vertical-align:-30%">
				<a href="http://www.google.com/calendar/render?cid=http://www.tourfilter.com/<%=@metro_code%>/ical"><img src="http://www.google.com/calendar/images/ext/gc_button1.gif" border=0></a>
			</span>
			</span>
			<a href="webcal://<%=host_and_port%>/<%=@metro_code%>/ical">Subscribe to all <%=@metro%>	 shows tracked by tourfilter users.</a></li>
	</ul>
<br>
