<div class="header1">
About iCal and iCalendar
</div>
<p>iCal is another name for a technology called iCalendar. iCalendar is the language that many calendars use to import and export events and appointments. There is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICalendar">very helpful wikipedia article</a> on the subject.</p>

<p>According to the article iCalendar is supported by the following calendaring applications:
<ul>
	<li>
 <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Computer" title="Apple Computer">Apple</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICal" title="ICal">iCal</a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chandler_%28PIM%29" title="Chandler (PIM)">Chandler</a>
	</li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lotus_Notes" title="Lotus Notes">Lotus Notes</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ScheduleWorld" title="ScheduleWorld">ScheduleWorld</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korganizer" title="Korganizer">Korganizer</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mozilla_Calendar" title="Mozilla Calendar">Mozilla Calendar</a> (including <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mozilla_Sunbird" title="Mozilla Sunbird">Mozilla Sunbird</a>)</li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mulberry_%28email_client%29" title="Mulberry (email client)">Mulberry</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ximian_Evolution" title="Ximian Evolution">Ximian Evolution</a></li><li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Kronolith&amp;action=edit" class="new" title="Kronolith">Kronolith</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simple_Groupware" title="Simple Groupware">Simple Groupware</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Calendar" title="Windows Calendar">Windows Calendar</a></li><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuvvo" title="Nuvvo">Nuvvo</a></li><li>to some extent, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Outlook" title="Microsoft Outlook">Microsoft Outlook</a> 
</ul>
</p>
<br>
<div class="header1">
Tourfilter in a widget
</div>
<p>
For the widget-hearted, you can download iCalendar widgets that will give you one-key access to your tourfilter calendar.
<ul>
<li>For Windows (2000 and up) AND Mac (OSX 10.3 and up) users, download the free Yahoo! Widget engine <a href="http://widgets.yahoo.com/">here</a>. It comes with an iCalendar widget.</li>

<li>For Mac users (OS X 10.4 and up), you just need to download Ben Kazez's <a href="http://www.benkazez.com/icalevents.php">iCal Events</a> widget.</li>
</ul>
</p>

